    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-03-06T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-03-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="31"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/3–652: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BDKE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruce</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-03-06T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 6, 1952—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5384. Rptd info Moscow 159, Saigon 310, Rome, London, Bonn, Berlin unn.</p>
                <p>Front page today’s <hi rend="italic">Humanité</hi> contains <gloss
                        target="#t_msg1">msg</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_CPF1">CPF</gloss> central comite signed Duclos<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d31fn1">
                        <persName>Jacques Duclos</persName>, Secretary of the French Communist
                        Party; President of the Communist Group in the National Assembly.</note> to
                    “Mr. President and dear comrade” <persName corresp="#p_HCM1">Ho Chi
                        Minh</persName> on occasion anniversary founding of Lien-Viet (League for
                    National Independence) congratulating him and his people on recent successes in
                    struggle for independence and peace. Central comite assures <persName
                        corresp="#p_HCM1">Ho</persName> of “active solidarity French people and
                    working class” and condemns criminal war whose aims are contrary to true
                    interests of France. Letter states defeat of French colonialists will at same
                    time strike heavy blow against Amer warmongers seeking to dominate world.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> off discussed this treasonable <gloss
                        target="#t_msg1">msg</gloss> with high <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> official who expressed indignation its publication,
                    particularly at this time when French policy Indochina subj such controversy,
                    but gave no clue whether govt considering taking any retaliatory steps.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
